1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:05,000
Relay turns one confirmed customer brief into multiple verifiable offers. Here is how.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,200
The Nuxt experience sends a Zod-validated brief to the NestJS API.

3
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:16,000
PostgreSQL stores an immutable version, then Relay writes the run and outbox event in one transaction.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:23,333
Redis and BullMQ move identifiers—not transcripts or secrets—to a retry-safe worker.

5
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:28,133
Provider adapters keep infrastructure replaceable. Google Places discovers businesses.

6
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:35,266
ElevenLabs runs calls. OpenAI structures outcomes. Private evidence lives in Supabase Storage.

7
00:00:35,266 --> 00:00:44,600
Deterministic policy normalizes fees, rejects unsupported leverage, and ranks only evidenced quotes.

8
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:51,666
Progress streams back so customers see calls, quote movement, and final reasoning as it happens.

9
00:00:51,666 --> 00:00:56,266
One immutable brief. Durable orchestration. Truthful negotiation. Verifiable decisions.
